\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Obliteration is the deepest pit and he is lying on his side at the bottom of it.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 His head is missing.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The ripped pieces of his heart float above his shoulder.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 A whole string of organs have become unstrung and float above his length like a clothesline; intestines, stomach, spleen, all black and dripping on his goosepricked skin.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Several gray boulders churn around in place beside him.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 His awareness floats out towards them, then back, then out and around, lurching, then back, and back, and out, and back, and on, and on, and on.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 I can\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t sleep, because if I close my eyes and stay still, I can feel the ripping. When you first learn that a hurting heart is not a metaphor.}}